More than 2,500 dogs, representing 118 breeds, will compete at Sunday's All Breed Dog 
Show and Obedience Trials at the Los Angeles Sports Arena.  They will undergo 
demonstrations and tests to show their skills.  This is a chance for all to learn about the 
possibilities, advantages and disadvantages of different breeds.  Other attractions include 
an expert who will answer behavioral questions about pets, free veterinary advice, a 
demonstration of how 4-H youngsters train puppies to become guide dogs and more than 
70 vendors selling dog paraphernalia.  A computer will enable visitors to determine 
which breeds would best suit their life styles.</SUM>

